{"title":"Paris-Nice 2024: Route, how to watch, start list and everything you need to know","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-nice-preview","date":1709136534000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-nice-preview\">Paris-Nice 2024: Route, how to watch, start list and everything you need to know</a></p>\n\n<p>Paris-Nice, nicknamed the Race to the Sun, is one of the biggest one-week stage races on the men’s WorldTour calendar with <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-route-live-tv-guide-startlist-stage-by-stage\" target=\"_blank\">Tour de France</a> hopefuls using it to test early season shape or just to get into the swing of things once more. The 2024 edition returns from 3rd-10th March.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Last year’s race was won by <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/tadej-pogacar\" target=\"_blank\">Tadej Pogačar</a> (UAE Team Emirates) by 53 seconds ahead of David Gaudu (<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/groupama-fdj\" target=\"_blank\">Groupama-FDJ</a>) and 1:39 over Jonas Vingegaard (<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/jumbo-visma\" target=\"_blank\">Visma-Lease a Bike</a>). Stage 6 was cancelled due to high wind speeds in the area as Pogačar dominated in the final two mountainous stages.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Pogačar won’t be back to defend his title as he’ll be racing in <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/strade-bianche-all-you-need-to-know\" target=\"_blank\">Strade Bianche</a>. <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/primoz-roglic\" target=\"_blank\">Primož Roglič</a> (Bora-Hansgrohe) and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/remco-evenepoel\" target=\"_blank\">Remco Evenepoel </a>(Soudal-QuickStep) will be on the start line with <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/uae-team-emirates\" target=\"_blank\">UAE Team Emirates</a> still bringing the firepower in João Almeida, Finn Fisher-Black, Brandon McNulty and Jay Vine.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/pro-log-marianne-vos-omloop-het-nieuwsblad\">Pro Log: Wout van Aert and Marianne Vos get debut wins, Adam Yates suffers concussion and ‘fraudulent’ Cynisca</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/cyclist-magazine-podcast-episode-21-the-king-sean-kelly\">Cyclist Magazine Podcast Episode 21 – The King, Sean Kelly</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/strade-bianche-all-you-need-to-know\">Strade Bianche 2024: New routes, how to watch and all you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-route-live-tv-guide-startlist-stage-by-stage\">Men’s Tour de France 2024 route announced: What will riders face on the road from Florence to Nice?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Paris-Nice 2024: Key information</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/PAris-Nice-2023-podium-close-970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/PAris-Nice-2023-podium-close-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/PAris-Nice-2023-podium-close-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/PAris-Nice-2023-podium-close-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/PAris-Nice-2023-podium-close-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/PAris-Nice-2023-podium-close-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/PAris-Nice-2023-podium-close-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/PAris-Nice-2023-podium-close-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/PAris-Nice-2023-podium-close-350x233.jpeg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/PAris-Nice-2023-podium-close.jpeg 1170w\" /><figcaption>Paris-Nice</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Date: </strong>3rd-10th March 2024<br /><strong>Start: </strong>Les Mureaux<br /><strong>Finish: </strong>Nice<br /><strong>Stages:</strong> 8<br /><strong>Distance: </strong>1,221km<br /><strong>2023 winner: </strong>Tadej Pogačar (UAE Team Emirates)<br /><strong>UK television coverage: </strong>Discovery+, Eurosport 2 (Highlights: ITV4)</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Paris-Nice 2024: The route</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-map-2024-970x970.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-map-2024-970x970.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-map-2024-300x300.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-map-2024-150x150.jpeg 150w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-map-2024-768x768.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-map-2024-1536x1536.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-map-2024-2048x2048.jpeg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-map-2024-75x75.jpeg 75w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-map-2024-350x350.jpeg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-map-2024-750x750.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-map-2024-1140x1140.jpeg 1140w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Beginning in Yvelines once again, the race will take riders down central France and towards the southeast to finish in Nice, also where the 2024 Tour de France will host its <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/2024-tour-de-france-nice-time-trial\" target=\"_blank\">final stage individual time-trial</a> in the summer.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Paris-Nice 2024: Stage-by-stage preview</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1, Sunday 3rd March: Les Mureaux – Les Mureaux, 157.7km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"960\" height=\"561\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-1.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-1.jpeg 960w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-1-300x175.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-1-768x449.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-1-750x438.jpeg 750w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The opening stage of the 2024 Paris-Nice is a day littered with short Category 3 climbs, the last one coming 12km before the finish.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2, Monday 4th March: Thoiry – Montargis, 179km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"960\" height=\"561\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-2.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-2.jpeg 960w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-2-300x175.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-2-768x449.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-2-750x438.jpeg 750w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s a flatter day for Stage 2, a sprinter’s playground for Arnaud De Lie (Lotto-Dstny), Olav Kooij (Visma-Lease a Bike) or powerhouse Mads Pederson (Lidl-Trek).</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3, Tuesday 5th March: Auxerre – Auxerre, 26.9km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"960\" height=\"561\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-3.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-3.jpeg 960w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-3-300x175.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-3-768x449.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-3-750x438.jpeg 750w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>There should be more team time-trials. Stage 3 is a slightly bumpy 26.9km ride around Auxerre. Last year’s TTT was won by Visma-Lease a Bike by one second ahead of EF Education-EasyPost.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 4, Wednesday 6th March: Chalon-sur-Saône – Mont Brouilly, 183km.</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"960\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-4.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-4.jpeg 960w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-4-300x202.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-4-768x518.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-4-750x505.jpeg 750w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Category 2 climbs rear their heads (or summits?) as the gradients begin to notch upwards. There’s six Cat 2 climbs in total including the summit finish on Mont Brouilly (3km, 7.7%). The Category 1 Col du Fût d’Avenas (5.1km, 7.3%) comes just after the only sprint point of the day.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 5, Thursday 7th March: Saint-Sauveur-de-Montagut – Sisteron, 193.5km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"960\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-5.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-5.jpeg 960w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-5-300x202.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-5-768x518.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-5-750x505.jpeg 750w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Another hilly day in the saddle. Stage 5 sees four Category 3 climbs on the road to Sisteron, the longest of the Col de Peyruergue (5.4km, 4.9%) coming 118km into the 193.5km day.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 6, Friday 8th March: Sisteron – La Colle-sur-Loup, 198.2km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"960\" height=\"674\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-6.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-6.jpeg 960w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-6-300x211.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-6-768x539.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-6-750x527.jpeg 750w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Picking up where yesterday’s stage left off in Sisteron, Stage 6 passes over five categorised climbs before a downhill finish towards La Colle-sur-Loup, a slight incline then hitting in the final kilometre before the finish line.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 7, Saturday 9th March: Nice – Auron, 173km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"960\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-7.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-7.jpeg 960w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-7-300x202.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-7-768x518.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-7-750x505.jpeg 750w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The hills turn to mountains. The peloton immediately face the Category 2 Côte de Gattières (4.5km, 4.8%) just 10km into the day, which culminates with a summit finish at the Category 1 Auron (7.3km, 7.2%).</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 8, Sunday 10th March: Nice – Nice, 109.5km.</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"960\" height=\"604\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-8.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-8.jpeg 960w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-8-300x189.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-8-768x483.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-2024-Stage-8-750x472.jpeg 750w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The final stage of Paris-Nice is a short but not sweet ride around Nice. A trio of Category 2 climbs precede two Category 1 behemoths that sandwich the short side of the Col d’Èze (which will feature in the Tour de France TT), with parts of the final climb of the Col des Quatre Chemins reaching 16% gradients.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Paris-Nice 2024: Live TV and streaming guide</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-sprint-finish-2023-970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-sprint-finish-2023-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-sprint-finish-2023-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-sprint-finish-2023-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-sprint-finish-2023-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-sprint-finish-2023-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-sprint-finish-2023-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-sprint-finish-2023-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-sprint-finish-2023-350x233.jpeg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/02/Paris-Nice-sprint-finish-2023.jpeg 1500w\" /><figcaption>Paris-Nice</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Paris-Nice 2024 will be available to watch in the UK on <a href=\"https://auth.discoveryplus.com/gb/product?flow=purchase&amp;videoAssetId=6021174\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a> for £6.99 per month with the basic package, which includes cycling and all other Eurosport programmes. It will also be shown on the TV channel Eurosport 2 in the UK.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s not being shown in your country, you may be able to watch coverage using a VPN – Virtual Private Network – which allows users to mask their IP address and watch geo-blocked content, provided they don’t need to pay for a subscription. This is also helpful for watching paid-for coverage while travelling abroad in countries without access.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One such example is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is very <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, helps users to find way to watch cycling without having to pay for broadcasters services, and costs £5.36 per month, with three months free. Other options include <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fnordvpn.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">NordVPN</a>, <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fsurfshark.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Surfshark</a> and <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kaspersky.co.uk%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Kapersky</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Paris-Nice international broadcasters</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Australia: </strong>SBS<br /><strong>Basque Country:</strong> EITB<br /><strong>Belgium: </strong>RTBF, VRT<br /><strong>Canada: </strong>FloBikes<br /><strong>China:</strong> Zhibo TV<br /><strong>Colombia: </strong>Caracol<br /><strong>Denmark: </strong>DKTV2<br /><strong>Europe:</strong> Eurosport<br /><strong>France:</strong> Eurosport, France 3<br /><strong>Italy: </strong>Rai Sport<br /><strong>Japan: </strong>J Sports<br /><strong>Latin America:</strong> ESPN International<br /><strong>Luxembourg: </strong>RTL<br /><strong>Middle East &amp; North Africa: </strong>beIN Sports<br /><strong>Netherlands: </strong>NOS<br /><strong>New Zealand: </strong>Sky Sport<br /><strong>Norway:</strong> TV2<br /><strong>South East Asia: </strong>Eurosport<br /><strong>Spain: </strong>Teledeporte<br /><strong>Sub-Saharan Africa: </strong>Supersport<br /><strong>Switzerland:</strong> SRG SSR<br /><strong>United States: </strong>NBC Sports</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Paris-Nice 2024 TV times</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 1, Sunday 3rd March</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Discovery+: 14:10 – 16:10<br />Eurosport 2: 15:10 – 17:00<br />ITV4 Highlights: 18:00 – 19:00</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 2, Monday 4th March</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Discovery+: 13:50 – 15:50<br />Eurosport 2: 15:45 – 16:45<br />ITV4 Highlights: 19:00 – 20:00</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 3, Tuesday 5th March</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Discovery+: 13:50 – 15:50<br />Eurosport 2: 15:45 – 16:45<br />ITV4 Highlights: 19:00 – 20:00</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 4, Wednesday 6th March</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Discovery+: 13:50 – 15:50<br />Eurosport 2: 15:45 – 16:45<br />ITV4 Highlights: 19:00 – 20:00</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 5, Thursday 7th March</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Discovery+: 13:50 – 15:50<br />Eurosport 2: 15:45 – 16:45<br />ITV4 Highlights: TBA</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 6, Friday 8th March</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Discovery+: 13:50 – 15:50<br />Eurosport 2: 15:45 – 16:45<br />ITV4 Highlights: TBA</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 7, Saturday 9th March</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Discovery+: 12:25 – 14:25<br />Eurosport 2: 13:25 – 15:15<br />ITV4 Highlights: TBA</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 8, Sunday 10th March</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Discovery+: 12:05 – 14:05 <br />Eurosport 2: 13:05 – 15:00<br />ITV4 Highlights: TBA</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Paris-Nice 2024: Start list</h2>\n\n\n\n<div><p><em>Data powered by <a href=\"https://firstcycling.com/race.php?r=2&amp;y=2024&amp;k=8\" target=\"_blank\">FirstCycling.com</a></em></p></div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-nice-preview\">Paris-Ni